    <string name="guide_accessibility">How to Play comic. Swipe left and right through eight illustrated pages.</string>
    <string name="guide_explore_title">Meet your little kingdom</string>
    <string name="guide_explore_body">Drag to look around, pinch to zoom, and tap discovered ground to move the royal kitten. Walking reveals permanent fog of war. Surveying every reachable shore also uncovers the inaccessible middle of lakes and rocks.</string>
    <string name="guide_explore_tip">Explore first: buildings can only be placed on discovered, reachable ground.</string>
    <string name="guide_first_buildings_title">A balanced first pair</string>
    <string name="guide_first_buildings_body">Begin with one Fishing Dock and one Catnip Farm. The two starting workers can build and operate them in parallel. Fish supports population growth; Fish plus Catnip lets the Town Hall hire the next worker.</string>
    <string name="guide_first_buildings_tip">Recommended opening: Fishing Dock → Catnip Farm. A second Dock can wait.</string>
    <string name="guide_construction_title">Construction needs paws</string>
    <string name="guide_construction_body">Placing a building creates a construction site, not a finished building. The closest free kitten walks beside it and completes each work stage. A site with an exclamation mark is safely waiting for a free builder.</string>
    <string name="guide_construction_tip">Production workers stay at their jobs. Release one when every kitten is busy.</string>
    <string name="guide_delivery_title">Goods must reach storage</string>
    <string name="guide_delivery_body">End Turn prepares a batch at every staffed workshop. Its icon appears above the building. The assigned kitten collects it, carries it across the map, and deposits it at the closest Town Hall or Storage Barn.</string>
    <string name="guide_delivery_tip">Only delivered goods appear in the top resource bar and can be spent.</string>
    <string name="guide_balance_title">Fish, Catnip, then growth</string>
    <string name="guide_balance_body">The Town Hall already houses four kittens, so an early Cottage is unnecessary. Keep one Dock and one Farm staffed. After deliveries, end turns: Fish pays gentle upkeep and eventually grows the population from two to three.</string>
    <string name="guide_balance_tip">Let workers finish delivery before ending another turn or trying to spend the batch.</string>
    <string name="guide_hiring_title">Hire at the Town Hall</string>
    <string name="guide_hiring_body">Tap the Town Hall and choose Hire Kitten. Hiring costs 5 Fish and 2 Catnip, and requires population to be greater than the current worker count. A new worker immediately takes the oldest waiting construction job.</string>
    <string name="guide_hiring_tip">A grey Hire button means you need resources or must wait for a new resident.</string>
    <string name="guide_recovery_title">No free builder? You are not stuck</string>
    <string name="guide_recovery_body">If both starting kittens work at two Docks, tap either Dock and choose Release Kitten. That kitten automatically leaves the Dock and builds the oldest waiting site. Build a Catnip Farm while the other Dock keeps fishing.</string>
    <string name="guide_recovery_tip">Releasing a worker never deletes the building or goods already waiting there.</string>
    <string name="guide_expansion_title">Grow one step at a time</string>
    <string name="guide_expansion_body">After hiring a third worker, add a Lumber Camp. Build a Cottage near the Town Hall housing limit, then a Storage Barn. Research unlocks weaving, scholars, plazas, crystals, and stronger yields; the World Map opens peaceful diplomacy.</string>
    <string name="guide_expansion_tip">There is no defeat timer. Pause, rebalance assignments, and grow at your own pace.</string>
